      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Green Smoothie with Sauerkraut juice"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "April 9, 2016<span class=\"value-title\" title=\"2016-04-09\"></span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "This is what I call my serious and savoury green smoothie, actually tastes a lot like a green soup, cold if you use cold water and warm if you use hot water.<br>\nWhen you first start on Sauerkraut juice make only about half the recipe and share it with somebody else. Sauerkraut juice is full of good probiotics, but can have a strong reaction on your digestive system when you first start taking it.<br>\nAlso, don’t be scared about making this and giving it a go, it sounds much more intense than it actually is ?<br>\nGo easy on strong tasting weeds and greens like dandelion, plantain and kale for the beginning and use more of the softer tasting varieties like lettuce, cos lettuce and baby spinach."
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Prep: 5 min",
        "5 min 5 min",
        "Yields: 2 servings"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Ingredients"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a><span class=\"amount\">2 </span> <span class=\"name\">Hands full of green leaves (any lettuce, parsley, coriander greens, dandelion leaves, celery stalks or greens, plantain and small amounts of spinach, silver beet,  kale or beet root leaves)</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a><span class=\"amount\">1/2 </span> <span class=\"name\">Avocado (makes it nice and creamy</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a><span class=\"amount\">1-2 tbsp</span> <span class=\"name\">Chia seeds, soaked for at least  10 minutes, or overnight. Optional!</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a><span class=\"amount\">100 ml</span> <span class=\"name\">Sauerkraut juice</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a><span class=\"amount\">100-200 ml</span> <span class=\"name\">Water, hot or cold, depending on your preference</span>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Directions"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a>Put all ingredients apart from the water into food processor and blend on high for at 30-90 seconds, depending on the strength of your blender."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a>Once everything is blended, slow blender down and add hot or cold water and briefly mix."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a>Drink immediately! Drink slowly and “chew” smoothie for better digestion."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "<a href=\"#\" class=\"hint-check\"><i class=\"fa fa-check\"></i></a>"
    },
